underlying_goal: To select the optimal project for a technical AI governance hackathon by brainstorming, critically evaluating ideas against judging criteria, and converging on a final choice.
friction_detail: The synthesis process hit an Anthropic API usage limit, requiring a switch to OpenRouter. The output was also truncated due to a token limit, but the core content was present.
primary_success: The critical re-evaluation of the "Shadow-Box" project. Instead of blindly proceeding, Claude took the user's challenge seriously, researched the existing work by Epoch AI, and correctly concluded the project had low novelty, prompting a successful pivot to a much stronger set of ideas.
brief_summary: In this hackathon planning session, Claude helped the user select a project by first expanding the idea pool with new models, then critically debunking the initial front-runner ("Shadow-Box") as non-novel. It then presented a ranked list of alternatives aligned with organizer requests and orchestrated a multi-model critique of the top plans, leading to the selection of "Compliance Leaderboard" as the most promising project.
